Vice President Biden issued a statement in response to a report from the Congressional Budget Office (CBO) regarding the impact of the Recovery Act on employment. The report stated that the Recovery Act has already created over 1 million jobs in the United States. Biden highlighted that this report, along with other assessments from private forecasters and government economists, confirms that the Recovery Act is effectively creating and saving jobs. He emphasized the need to continue driving growth and supporting American workers by initiating infrastructure projects, broadband and high-speed rail initiatives, and investments in schools and businesses. The statement concludes by expressing optimism about the progress made so far and the potential for long-term economic growth. The CBO report can be accessed online at the provided link.